Defendant James R Strehlow in court with attorney Craig Michael Kuhary.  Shawn N Woller appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant enters a guilty plea as to 1. Count 4 is dismissed outright. Counts 2 and 3 are dismissed and read-in.  Court imposed the following sentence:

  The defendant was sentenced to the following:

HUBER:  210 days, released for work/treatment (Credit - 3 days). Sentence to commence today.

FINE: $2023.00 (to be paid at the rate of $100.00 month commencing 05/01/2016 or serve 26 days jail, consecutive, as penalty for non payment of fine);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00, to be paid at $100.00 month consecutive to payment of fine or to be converted to a civil judgment for non payment of surcharge.

BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $40.00 paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forward to Waukesha County Sheriff Department or to be converted to a civil judgment for non payment of fee.

Defendant to pay $100.00 a month commencing 05/01/2016 or alternate of 26 days jail. Apply any bail that is posted. 

D/L REVOCATION: 33 months;

IGNITION INTERLOCK: 33 months;

Other:  AODA ASSESSMENT AND FOLLOW THROUGH.
